The paper focuses on motion planning for aerial robots, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The use of Euclidean Signed Distance Field (ESDF) and the proposed mapping system FIESTA involve computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The optimization and performance evaluation of the algorithm can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY).
